House Resolution 775
By: Representatives Carter of the 93rd, Bennett of the 94th, and Hugley of the 141st
A RESOLUTION
1 Recognizing and commending Carlene Anderson; and for other purposes.
2 WHEREAS, Carlene Anderson has demonstrated an unwavering commitment to education,
3 civic engagement, and student empowerment through her decades of service as an educator,
4 mentor, and community advocate; and
5 WHEREAS, she began her exemplary career as an educator in 2002 through the teacher
6 training program at William Paterson University and joined the Paterson Public School
7 System, where she incorporated her social work background into her teaching practice to
8 promote innovation and digital citizenship at the elementary level; and
9 WHEREAS, her efforts earned her multiple grants from the Perloff Family Foundation and
10 the Garden State Partnership for Teacher Quality as well as national recognition through
11 features on NJEA's Classroom Closeup-NJ and One-on-One with Steve Adubato; and
12 WHEREAS, she presented her projects at prominent conferences such as the International
13 Society for Technology in Education, the Society for Information Technology and Teacher
14 Education, and the National Association of Professional Development Schools; and
