15 WHEREAS, after relocating to Georgia in 2014, she joined Gwinnett County Public Schools
16 and served as a teacher of exceptional learners with the Georgia Network for Educational and
17 Therapeutic Support North Metro Program, where her students won awards at the GCPS
18 Media Festival for digital storytelling projects; and
19 WHEREAS, following injuries in 2019 that required her to leave the classroom, she
20 continued her advocacy work as president of the local units of her son's Parent Teacher
21 Student Associations, where she now champions student mental health, school safety,
22 education equity, access to nutrition, and grassroots civic action; and
23 WHEREAS, Carlene Anderson is a breast cancer survivor who endured surgery,
24 chemotherapy, and radiation from July 2023 to January 2024, emerging stronger and more
25 determined than ever to continue making an impact through faith, resilience, and service.
26 NOW, THEREFORE, BE IT RESOLVED BY THE HOUSE OF REPRESENTATIVES that
27 the members of this body recognize and commend Carlene Anderson for her many
28 outstanding contributions on behalf of the youth of this state and beyond as well as extend
29 best wishes for future health, happiness, and success.
30 BE IT FURTHER RESOLVED that the Clerk of the House of Representatives is authorized
31 and directed to make an appropriate copy of this resolution available for distribution to
32 Carlene Anderson.
